snippet.textDisplay: The last "mistake" in Coco isn't really a mistake. It is merely a perspective issue. As the camera shifts to a closer view of the window you have a wider view of the wall behind the boy, while in the long shot you cannot see much of the wall behind him. You can experience this yourself by looking into your neighbor's window from across the street and then walking up and peering in with your face pressed against the glass...although you should probably let your neighbor know first to avoid traumatizing them.
